  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reduction of excess morbidity and mortality of affected populations in the North West and South West regions of Cameroon through emergency humanitarian assistance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to reduce excessive morbidity and mortality among the affected populations in the North West region and South West region affected by conflict. This WHO project provides timely access to essential health care, quality sexual reproductive health services, mental health care and psychosocial support, and strengthen epidemiological surveillance and the response to outbreaks. The project provides life-saving assistance to 370,500 people, including 70,395 women, 85,215 men, 214,890 children, and 19,500 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
